# Wine Conference App - Environment Variables
# ============================================
# This app uses Netlify Functions for AI features.
# All user data is stored locally in the browser (localStorage).

# ===========================================
# REQUIRED API KEYS
# ===========================================

# Anthropic API Key - Powers all AI text generation (Claude)
# Get your key from: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# Perplexity API Key - Powers intelligent website scraping
# Get your key from: https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=pplx-your-key-here


# ===========================================
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
# ===========================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Add your API keys above
#
# 3. Install dependencies:
#    npm install
#
# 4. Run the development server:
#    npm run dev
#
# ===========================================
# NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT
# ===========================================
#
# 1. Push your code to GitHub
#
# 2. Connect the repo to Netlify
#
# 3. In Netlify dashboard, go to:
#    Site Settings > Environment Variables
#
# 4. Add these variables:
#    ANTHROPIC_API_KEY = sk-ant-your-key
#    PERPLEXITY_API_KEY = pplx-your-key
#
# 5. Deploy! Netlify builds and serves everything automatically
#
# ===========================================
# HOW THE APP WORKS
# ===========================================
#
# AI Text Generation (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY):
#   - Tasting notes generation
#   - Event marketing copy
#   - Sales analysis insights
#   - Staff training scripts
#   - All Lightning Lab tools
#
# Website Scraping (PERPLEXITY_API_KEY):
#   - Extracts winery info from URLs
#   - Finds wines, varieties, location, etc.
#   - Uses Perplexity's online search capability
#
# Data Storage (NO backend needed):
#   - All saved items stored in browser localStorage
#   - Poll responses stored locally
#   - Beta signups stored locally
#   - Session persists until browser data cleared
#
# Fallback Mode:
#   - If API keys missing or calls fail, app shows sample data
#   - Users can still explore all features with demo content
